Forward Antoine Griezmann has been ruled out of France&#8217;s friendly game against Ivory Coast on Tuesday because of a foot injury, the French soccer federation (FFF) said on Sunday.Griezmann picked up the injury during Les Bleus&#8217; 2-1 victory over Sweden in a World Cup Group A qualifier on Friday.He has been released to his club, Atletico Madrid, and no player has been called up to replace him for the match in Lens, the FFF added.-Reuters